    "Name": "Assault Squad",
    "Content": "Assault squads are [[0b10]] aligned [[Squad|squads]] that are sent after Cogmind as a result of having too high [[Alert]]. Assaults are sent directly to Cogmind's position with [[Perfect Tracking]] and cannot be easily shaken. They consist of a single [[C-30 ARC]] typically containing 5 bots inside. If Cogmind has 3 or more allies, up to 2 additional bots may be sent to escort the ARC as additional firepower. Assault squads can be both Enumerated and Recalled at [[Terminal|Terminals]].\nAn alert indicates whenever an Assault squad is dispatched. Additionally, the log will display a message like [[GameText]]ALERT: Significant disruption in zone 9B, assault force dispatched[[/GameText]]. If more than one ARC was sent, the message will instead indicate [[GameText]]multiple assault carriers dispatched[[/GameText]].\n[[Heading]]Lore[[/Heading]]\n[[Lore]]WAR.Sys Records|Assault Squad[[/Lore]]\n[[Heading]]Frequency and Number[[/Heading]]\nAssaults may be dispatched regularly as Cogmind is at least Alert level 2 or 400 influence, although at lower Alert levels Assaults are rare. At Alert levels well above 1000, Assaults may be sent out at nearly opportunity. A higher Alert level also increases the chances of multiple ARCs being dispatched. In [[Materials]], Assaults can be dispatched every 400 turns on -9 and -8. In [[Factory]] and above, this changes to be every 250 turns. If an Assault would be dispatched at the same time an [[Extermination Squad]] would be dispatched, the Assault is delayed by 50 turns. Most assault waves consists of 1-2 ARCs, but at Alert levels in excess of 5X/1600 influence, 3 or even more ARCs can be sent.\n[[Heading:2]]During [[High Security|High]] or [[Maximum Security]][[/Heading]]\nThe frequency, number, and contents of ARCs changes. Assault forces with stronger compositions than usual may be dispatched in these conditions, although these ARCs only have 4 bots inside rather than the typical 5. 4 ARCs will be dispatched 100 turns into High Security and after another 100 turns. After that, 2 more ARCs will be added to each wave, but 50 more turns will be added in between the dispatch of each wave. The sizes of the Assault waves will also start to increase each wave, and the duration between each wave will increase. Maximum Security is similar, but with 6 ARCs to start the first 2 waves. The 2nd wave of Assaults in High Security and all subsequent waves, and all waves of Maximum Security may contain stronger than usual bots in them.\n[[Heading]]Assault Contents[[/Heading]]\n[[Image]]Assault Contents.png|Example contents of an Assault squad ARC[[/Image]]\nAssault contents can vary by depth, but their makeups are always similar. Assaults will always contain 4 combat bots and 1 support-type bot. The combat bots may become stronger under heavy assault conditions, but the possible support bots are always the same.\n\n[[Heading:2]]Normal Combat bots[[/Heading]]\n[[Table]]Depth|[[Brawler]]|[[Duelist]]|[[Grunt]]||-10|N/A|N/A|[[G-34 Mercenary]], squad leader [[G-47 Trooper]]||-9|[[B-36 Bruiser]]|[[L-31 Rogue]]|G-34 Mercenary, squad leader G-47 Trooper||-8|B-36 Bruiser|L-31 Rogue|G-47 Trooper, squad leader [[G-50 Soldier]]||-7|[[B-48 Gladiator]]|[[L-41 Fighter]]|G-47 Trooper, squad leader G-50 Soldier||-6|B-48 Gladiator|L-41 Fighter|G-50 Soldier, squad leader [[G-67 Veteran]]||-5|[[B-60 Warrior]]|L-41 Fighter|G-50 Soldier, squad leader G-67 Veteran||-4|B-60 Warrior|[[L-61 Swordsman]]|G-67 Veteran, squad leader [[G-73 Enforcer]]||-3|[[B-74 Champion]]|L-61 Swordsman|G-67 Veteran, squad leader G-73 Enforcer||-2|B-74 Champion|L-61 Swordsman|G-73 Enforcer||-1|B-74 Champion|L-61 Swordsman|G-73 Enforcer[[/Table]]\n[[Heading:2]]Strong assault combat bots (High/Max sec only)[[/Heading]]\n[[Table]]Depth|[[Executioner]]|[[Hunter]]|[[Investigator]]|[[Programmer]]|[[Striker]]||-10|N/A|N/A|N/A|N/A|N/A||-9|N/A|N/A|N/A|N/A|N/A||-8|N/A|N/A|N/A|N/A|N/A||-7|N/A|[[H-55 Commando]]|N/A|[[P-60 Hacker]]|N/A||-6|N/A|[[H-66 Slayer]]|N/A|P-60 Hacker|N/A||-5|N/A|H-66 Slayer|N/A|[[P-70 Sage]]|N/A||-4|N/A|[[H-77 Assassin]]|N/A|P-70 Sage|N/A||-3|Yes|H-77 Assassin|Yes|[[P-80 Master]]|Yes||-2|Yes|H-77 Assassin|Yes|P-80 Master|Yes||-1|Yes|H-77 Assassin|Yes|P-80 Master|Yes[[/Table]]\n[[Heading:2]]Utility bots[[/Heading]]\n[[Table]]Depth|[[E-15 Imp]]|[[Mechanic]]|[[Protector]]||-10|N/A|[[M-13 Machinist]]|N/A||-9|N/A|M-13 Machinist|[[I-25 Savior]]||-8|N/A|M-13 Machinist|I-25 Savior||-7|N/A|[[M-28 Smith]]|[[I-36 Angel]]||-6|Yes|M-28 Smith|I-36 Angel||-5|Yes|M-28 Smith|[[I-47 Archangel]]||-4|Yes|[[M-36 Artificer]]|I-47 Archangel||-3|Yes|M-36 Artificer|I-47 Archangel||-2|Yes|M-36 Artificer|I-47 Archangel||-1|Yes|M-36 Artificer|I-47 Archangel[[/Table]]\n[[Heading:2]]Additional bots with allies[[/Heading]]\n[[Table]]Depth|[[Demolisher]]|Programmer|[[Specialist]]||-10|N/A|N/A|N/A||-9|N/A|N/A|N/A||-8|[[D-53 Grenadier]]|N/A|N/A||-7|D-53 Grenadier|P-60 Hacker|[[X-57 Shotgunner]], [[X-62 Marksman]], [[X-67 Chaingunner]]||-6|D-53 Grenadier|P-60 Hacker|X-62 Marksman, X-67 Chaingunner, [[X-72 Disruptor]]||-5|[[D-63 Destroyer]]|P-70 Sage|X-67 Chaingunner, X-72 Disruptor, [[X-77 Beamer]]||-4|D-63 Destroyer|P-70 Sage|X-72 Disruptor, X-77 Beamer, [[X-82 Rainmaker]]||-3|D-63 Destroyer|P-80 Master|X-77 Beamer, X-82 Rainmaker, [[X-87 Electro]]||-2|[[D-83 Annihilator]]|P-80 Master|X-82 Rainmaker, X-87 Electro||-1|D-83 Annihilator|P-80 Master|X-87 Electro[[/Table]]\n[[Spoiler]][[Heading]][[Data Miner]] redirection[[/Heading]]\nThe Data Miner can redirect Assaults if his help is obtained by visiting his [[Data Miner (Location)|hideout]]. If redirected, Assaults will roam around a random area of the map rather than head directly to Cogmind's location. The Data Miner has a 50% chance to direct each ARC as part of an Assault about 15 turns after each Assault is dispatched. Redirection can only occur when High/Maximum Security is not active. If a redirect happens, the alert [[GameText]]Higher priority target acquired, redirecting assault.[[/GameText]] will be displayed. If an Assault is not redirected, there is a further 50% chance that the contents may be redirected after the ARC opens up. This can happen within 30 turns of the ARC opening. This effect will only redirect the squad leader, and the squad leader will only leave if currently unable to see Cogmind. All the remaining squad bots will continue to follow Cogmind. The true practical effect here is that if the squad forgets where Cogmind is, they will patrol around the redirected location rather than the location that the ARC opened.[[/Spoiler]]"
