    "Name": "Cargo Convoy",
    "Content": "[[Image]]Cargo Convoy.png|Intact cargo convoy[[/Image]]\n[[Image]]Cargo Convoy Deployed.png|A cargo convoy with ARCs deployed[[/Image]]\nCargo convoys are a special form of [[Transport Squad|transport squads]] that can be found from -7 to -2 on main [[Factory]] and [[Research]] floors. They consist of a single [[A-27 Freighter]], a [[Protector]], and two [[C-30 ARC|C-30 ARCs]] full of 4 combat bots and an extra utility bot, similar to strong [[Assault Squad|assaults]]. The parts contained within a Freighter are all [[Prototype Part|prototype]] or [[Authchips]], never faulty, and can be up to 3 ratings out of depth. For example, on -7, Haulers can contain up to rating 4 prototype parts. A cargo convoy Freighter can carry rating 5-7 prototype parts.\nCargo convoys are always preceeded by 3-5 [[Swarmer|Swarmers]] that scout out the path of the convoy before it appears. The alert [[GameText]]Cargo convoy en route, clear transfer corridor.[[/GameText]] will indicate when this is happening. A few turns later, the Freighter and guards will appear and take the same route.\nCargo convoys will always appear at a 0b10 controlled exit and head to a [[Garrison (Machine)|Garrison]]. Typically the Freighter leads the way and stays ahead of the Protector and ARCs, which normally trail a few tiles behind. A [[Transport Network Coupler]] or [[Modified TNC]] will reveal the planned path of the Freighter. The Modified TNC will also show the contents of the Freighter. The Manifests hack will also show all the parts contained by the Freighter.\n[[Heading]]Attack response[[/Heading]]\nIf a cargo convoy is attacked, a message will indicate this, as well as an alert: [[GameText]]ALERT: Cargo convoy interrupted, initiating access lockdown.[[/GameText]] 100 turns after this, a [[Heavy]] will spawn at an 0b10 controlled exit or Garrison every 100 turns until all exits are guarded by a Heavy. Heavies may head toward a far away [[Caves]] exit in order to guard it. The Freighter will begin running away in a random direction when attacked. If it is not destroyed, it will head toward another nearby 0b10 controlled exit.\n[[Heading]][[Derelict]] attack[[/Heading]]\n[[Image]]Cargo Convoy Attack.png|Derelicts from a Garrison ready to assault a convoy[[/Image]]\nThere is a chance that Derelicts will decide to attack a cargo convoy. The chance is higher at lower depths. If they attack, they will appropriate a Garrison machine, rig some [[Dirty Bomb Trap|Dirty Bomb Traps]], and attack the convoy guards. If they are successful, they will retreat and leave the loot available for Cogmind. This may happen even if Cogmind is nowhere near the convoy. It may be a good idea to track the Freighter position in case this happens, even if not planning to attack the convoy directly, since this can often result in lots of powerful free loot. If Cogmind is not close enough to grab the loot, [[Recycler|Recyclers]] may have carried it off to a nearby [[Recycling Machine]]. Make sure to check these if the Freighter's stash can't be found nearby.\n[[Heading]]Convoy contents[[/Heading]]\n[[Table]]Depth|[[E-15 Imp]]|[[Executioner]]|[[Hunter]]|[[Mechanic]]|[[Programmer]]|Protector|[[Specialist]]|[[Striker]]||-7|N/A|N/A|[[H-55 Commando]]|[[M-28 Smith]]|[[P-60 Hacker]]|[[I-36 Angel]]|[[X-57 Shotgunner]], [[X-62 Marksman]], or [[X-67 Chaingunner]]|N/A||-6|Yes|N/A|[[H-66 Slayer]]|M-28 Smith|P-60 Hacker|I-36 Angel|X-62 Marksman, X-67 Chaingunner, or [[X-72 Disruptor]]|N/A||-5|Yes|N/A|H-66 Slayer|M-28 Smith|[[P-70 Sage]]|[[I-47 Archangel]]|X-67 Chaingunner, X-72 Disruptor, or [[X-77 Beamer]]|N/A||-4|Yes|Yes|[[H-77 Assassin]]|[[M-36 Artificer]]|P-70 Sage|I-47 Archangel|X-72 Disruptor, X-77 Beamer, or [[X-82 Rainmaker]]|Yes||-3|Yes|Yes|H-77 Assassin|M-36 Artificer|[[P-80 Master]]|I-47 Archangel|X-77 Beamer, X-82 Rainmaker, or [[X-87 Electro]]|Yes||-2|Yes|Yes|[[H-88 Terminator]]|M-36 Artificer|P-80 Master|I-47 Archangel|X-82 Rainmaker or X-87 Electro|Yes[[/Table]]"
